在placement exam 10里面，最后一道题会用到动态规划处理进而降低复杂度，这个文件是Pro Tay补充讲解的有关动态规划的课件，还有1道补充练习，题目如下
Assignments by Wednesday 2pm: Dynamic Programming Problem - Minimum Number of Coins
A small vending machine accepts only four types of coins {2-cent coin, 3-cent coin, 4-cent coin, 5-cent coin}. A customer wants to buy an item costing 16 cents.
Your task is to write a program using the dynamic programming  method to determine the minimum number of coins needed to make exactly 16 cents using the given coin denominations {2, 3, 4, 5}.
Your program should print out the minimum number of coins required, and the set of the actual coins used.
 
Once this is done, modify your program to print out multiple solutions: {2,4,5,5},
{5,4,4,3}, {4,4,4,4}, {5,5,3,3}.
 
Do not print repeated permutations: e.g., {5,3,5,3} is same as {3,5,3,5} and {5,5,3,3} and so on.
 
To avoid duplicate permutations (e.g., {5, 3, 5, 3} versus {3, 5, 5, 3}), you can enforce an ordering rule, i.e., always choose coins in non-decreasing order value. This portion will be easier if it is recursive.
